{"title_page": "Come Clarity (song)", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=October 2009}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Come Clarity\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[In Flames]]\n| album      = [[Come Clarity]]\n| A-side     = Come Clarity\n| B-side     = [[Only for the Weak]]\n| released   = 13 December 2006\n| format     = {{blist|[[Compact Disc|CD]] ([[Single (Music)|single]])|[[Phonograph record|vinyl]] ([[Extended play|EP]])}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Alternative metal]]\n| length     = 4:15\n| label      = [[Ferret Music]], [[Black Lodge Records|Black Lodge]]\n| writer     = [[Anders Frid\u00e9n]], [[Bj\u00f6rn Gelotte]], [[Jesper Str\u00f6mblad]]\n| producer   = Anders Frid\u00e9n, Bj\u00f6rn Gelotte, Jesper Str\u00f6mblad\n| prev_title = [[The Quiet Place]]\n| prev_year  = 2004\n| next_title = [[The Mirror's Truth]]\n| next_year  = 2008\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = Vinyl cover\n | type    = EP\n | cover   = Come Clarity - EP.jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption =\n}}\n}}\n\n\u201c'''Come Clarity'''\u201d is a song by Swedish [[Heavy metal music|metal]] band [[In Flames]] from their studio album ''[[Come Clarity]].'' It was released on 13 December 2006 and came in both a [[Single (music)|single]] and a limited [[Extended play|EP]] version. \n\nThe song does not feature In Flames' iconic [[melodic death metal]] sound, instead having a more traditional [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]] sound, influenced by bands like [[Iron Maiden]] and [[Black Sabbath]].  \n\n== Release ==\nThe CD single release only contains the title track itself and its video version.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/de/In-Flames-Come-Clarity/release/4473475|title=In Flames - Come Clarity|last=|first=|date=|website=Discogs|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref> A limited edition [[Phonograph record|vinyl record]] was also released (officially as an EP), and features \"Come Clarity\" as well as the song \"Only for the Weak\", taken from the 2000 album ''[[Clayman]]''. The cover of the vinyl issue shows In Flames' [[mascot]], the [[In Flames#Jester Head mascot|Jester Head]]; the first In Flames release since ''[[Clayman]]'' to do so.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| headline = CD single\n| title1 = Come Clarity\n| length1 = 4:15\n| title2 = Come Clarity\n| length2 = \n| note2 = video\n| all_writing =\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline  = Vinyl EP\n| title1    = Come Clarity\n| length1   = 4:15\n| title2    = Only for the Weak\n| length2   = 4:55\n| total_length = 9:10\n}}\n\n==Music video==\nThe video was directed by Lex Halaby.<ref name=\"video\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hdUzI2JxhfU|title=In Flames - Come Clarity (Official Video)|accessdate=August 14, 2011}}</ref> It shows lead vocalist [[Anders Frid\u00e9n]] driving his car, and after a while spotting a girl who's looking for a ride. As the band plays the song, there are scenes of both the girl walking in the desert and Anders driving by her. After the song's solo, a meteor shower occurs when the chorus comes back in. As the video starts to come to an end, Anders' is repeatedly shown driving, then eventually pulling over to pick the girl up. After pulling over, the girl disappears, leaving only a teddy bear that she was holding behind.\n\n==Personnel==\n\n* [[Anders Frid\u00e9n]] \u2013 [[singing|vocals]]\n* [[Jesper Str\u00f6mblad]] \u2013 [[guitar]]\n* [[Bj\u00f6rn Gelotte]] \u2013 guitar\n* [[Peter Iwers]] \u2013 [[bass guitar]]\n* [[Daniel Svensson]] \u2013 [[drum kit|drums]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.inflames.com In Flames\u2019 official website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080515112607/http://www.blacklodge.se/ Black Lodge Records\u2019 official website]\n\n{{In Flames}}\n\n[[Category:In Flames songs]]\n[[Category:2006 singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jesper Str\u00f6mblad]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=October 2009}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Come Clarity\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[In Flames]]\n| album      = [[Come Clarity]]\n| A-side     = Come Clarity\n| B-side     = [[Only for the Weak]]\n| released   = 13 December 2006\n| format     = {{blist|[[Compact Disc|CD]] ([[Single (Music)|single]])|[[Phonograph record|vinyl]] ([[Extended play|EP]])}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Alternative metal]]\n| length     = 4:15\n| label      = [[Ferret Music]], [[Black Lodge Records|Black Lodge]]\n| writer     = [[Anders Frid\u00e9n]], [[Bj\u00f6rn Gelotte]], [[Jesper Str\u00f6mblad]]\n| producer   = Anders Frid\u00e9n, Bj\u00f6rn Gelotte, Jesper Str\u00f6mblad\n| prev_title = [[The Quiet Place]]\n| prev_year  = 2004\n| next_title = [[The Mirror's Truth]]\n| next_year  = 2008\n| misc       = {{Extra album cover\n | header  = Vinyl Cover\n | type    = EP\n | cover   = Come Clarity - EP.jpg\n | border  =\n | alt     =\n | caption =\n}}\n}}\n\n\u201c'''Come Clarity'''\u201d is a song by Swedish [[Heavy metal music|metal]] band [[In Flames]] from their studio album ''[[Come Clarity]].'' It was released on 13 December 2006 and came in both a [[Single (music)|single]] and a limited [[Extended play|EP]] version. \n\nThe song does not feature In Flames' iconic [[melodic death metal]] sound, instead having a more traditional [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]] sound, influenced by bands like [[Iron Maiden]] and [[Black Sabbath]].  \n\n== Release ==\nThe CD single release only contains the title track itself and its video version.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/de/In-Flames-Come-Clarity/release/4473475|title=In Flames - Come Clarity|last=|first=|date=|website=Discogs|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-24}}</ref> A limited edition [[Phonograph 